title: m6a_seiran
body:
The [b]Aichi M6A [i]Seiran[/i][/b] was a rare late World War II Japanese seaplane bomber with a compact, folding design and high performance. It was designed for operation from the huge I-400 class submarine aircraft carriers, making it the only piloted, submarine-launched, dedicated strike aircraft ever to enter service. No M6A ever saw combat, the type's sole operational mission having been aborted by the end of the Pacific War. Twenty-nine examples were built of which only one survives today, in the Smithsonian National Air and Space Museum in the United States.

The M6A was a low-winged monoplane with a 1,400 horespower liquid-cooled V12 engine, bearing a more-than-coincidental resemblance to the D4Y [i]Suisei[/i] carrier-based dive bomber which Aichi was already manufacturing under license. The two man crew consisted of a pilot and an observer sitting behind him who navigated, operated the radio, and fired the plane's defensive armament of a single 13mm machine gun in a flexible mount. The aircraft was launched by catapult and could be reconfigured in the field to use two floats for landing and recovering at sea, or no undercarriage for improved performance at the cost of sacrificing the aircraft and possibly its crew after the mission. It carried either a single 850 kg torpedo or an equivalent weight of bombs.

Perhaps more than any other Axis "wonder weapon", the Seiran combined a complex and imaginative operational concept, impressive technical achievements, and a complete lack of attention to the rational allocation of scarce resources relative to the results it could hope to achieve. It is therefore not surprising that it was a pet project of admiral [[Yamamoto Isoroku]], who was notorious for bypassing staff analysis to pursue his chosen schemes. That said, late-war technologies unavailable to the Japanese meant that the I-400/Seiran combination became an important precursor to the U.S. Navy's experimental 'Loon' and operational 'Regulus' submarine-launched nuclear cruise missiles.

"Cross-Cupped Wine"

title: super_sass
body:
The ArmaLite SUPER SASS (Semi Automatic Sniper System) was developed by ArmaLite Inc. and submitted as an entry for the XM110 competition, which was announced by the military in November of 2004.

Although ArmaLite’s entry was not selected by the military, the company continued development and introduced what it calls the Super SASS in .308 Winchester at the 2006 SHOT Show for commercial sales. As to be expected, this new model is based upon ArmaLite’s well-known AR-10 action.

title: cat_shit_one
body:
Cat Shit One is a three volume manga series written and illustrated by [[Kobayashi Motofumi]]. It was originally published in Japan in 1998 by Softbank Publishing.

The manga follows three American soldiers in the Vietnam War named Botasky, Packy and Rats. All three are in the recon team called Cat Shit One. 

The depiction of Americans as rabbits is actually a pun on the Japanese word for rabbit. The Japanese word for rabbit is "うさぎ", which can be romanized as "usagi", or USA GI.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Cat Shit One":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cat_Shit_One

title: magnezone
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #462 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Electric/Steel Pokémon.
Magnezone is the result of Magneton leveling up in the presence of a special magnetic field. The evolution is done on a molecular level, but despite this, scientists have failed at attempts to force it. 

It evolves from [[Magneton]] when leveled up in: 
Gen IV: "Mt. Coronet":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mt._Coronet
Gen V:  "Chargestone Cave":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Chargestone_Cave
Gen VI: "Route 13 (Kalos)":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Kalos_Route_13 ([[pokemon_xy|Pokémon XY]]) and "New Mauville":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/New_Mauville ([[pokemon_oras|Pokémon Oras]])
Japanese Name: [b]Jibacoil[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Weavile]]
Next Pokémon: [[Lickilicky]]

title: qianshou_guanyin
body:
Chinese (traditional / simplified): 千手觀音[菩薩] / 千手观音[菩萨] (Qian shou Guan yin [Pusa])
Japanese: 千手観音[菩薩] (せんじゅかんのん; Senju Kannon [Bosatsu])

Literally, "[[Guanyin]] with A Thousand Arms". A "bodhisattva":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodhisattva] known in East Asian [[Buddhism]].
Characterized by the statues' [[extra_arms|many (usually forty-two) arms]] and [[extra_faces|several (eleven in most cases) faces]].
Often being called some other names. E.g.: 千手千眼[觀世音菩薩/観世音菩薩/观世音菩萨] ("Guanshiyin Bodhisattva With A Thousand Arms and Thousand eyes")

title: van_fanel
body: The main hero of [[Tenkuu no Escaflowne]], Van is the prince of Fanel who pilots the mecha [[Escaflowne]] and fights to defend his land from the Zaibach Empire, but is a pacifist at heart. He is responsible for transporting [[Kanzaki Hitomi]] to Gaea and promises to help her return.

title: kanzaki_hitomi
body: The main heroine of [[Tenkuu no Escaflowne]], Hitomi is a high school girl who is transported to the land of Gaea. She becomes involved in [[Van Fanel]]'s war against the Zaibach Empire, and becomes critical in unlocking [[Escaflowne]]'s true potential.

title: fidget_spinner
body:
A fidget spinner is a type of [[toy]], whose marketers claim it relieves stress. A basic fidget spinner consists of a bearing in the center of a design made from any of a variety of materials including brass, stainless steel, titanium, copper and plastic. The object exploded in popularity during the first half of 2017.

h4. External links

* Wikipedia: "Fidget spinner":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fidget_spinner]

title: wang_mang_(moeoh_ex)
body:
[quote]
[i]Xin Dynasty's science is the best in the world![/i]

--- Wang Mang
[/quote]

A [[Moeoh EX]] character, modeled after "Wang Mang":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wang_Mang], the sole emperor of the Xin/Hsin Dynasty.
She is a time traveller from 21st century.
(Although the historical Wang Mang believed the ancient "Zhou dynasty":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zhou_dynasty] was the ideal governmental structure, some of his reforms have been said to be a foreshadowing of socialism.)

h4.See also

* "MoeGirl Wiki":[https://zh.moegirl.org/%E8%90%8C%E7%8E%8BEX:%E7%8E%8B%E8%8E%BD]

title: ootsuki_makoto
body:
The young man who confesses his love to Mikoto. 16 years old.

[spoiler]Much more unhinged than he initially appears with a very twisted view of romance. States that he likes her most when she is hating him, and would actually prefer that she not develop romantic feelings for him.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]Hence the roughly translated title: [i]To The Hateful You, I Like You.[/i][/spoiler]

[spoiler]Why he has become the way he is - that is to say volatile, unpredictable, abusive and [i]irredeemably vulgar[/i] in his expression of 'love' yet oddly sweet to Mikoto -  is assumed to be revealed later throughout the story.[/spoiler]

title: shirakawa_mikoto
body:
The girl that Makoto professes his love to. 16 years old with trademark [[Sanpaku]] eyes and bushy red hair. Seemingly an unassuming victim of circumstance.

[spoiler]Despite never having had a boyfriend or having been asked out before, she is proud in maintaining her girlfriend status with Makoto to show him off to her friends and is intent on up-keeping appearances despite his [i]abominable[/i] behavior.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]Gradually corrupted by Makoto's influence and develops what is speculated to be a mild case of autassassinophilia - a fetish in which someone is sexually aroused by fantasizing about, or being involved in, situations in which may end in their death.[/spoiler]

title: toyota_sports_800
body: [[Toyota]] Motor Corporation's first production sports car. The prototype for the Sports 800, called the Toyota Publica Sports, debuted at the 1962 Tokyo Auto Show, featuring a space age sliding canopy and utilizing the 21 kW (28 hp) power train of the Toyota Publica 700, a Japanese market economy car. The Toyota Sports 800 is affectionately called the "Yota-Hachi" (ヨタハチ), which is a Japanese short form for "Toyota 8".
